## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="a13db-189">Controlar la <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource.ContextCreating> eventos para proporcionar sus propios <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> en lugar de tener un nuevo <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> creado.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a13db-189">Handle the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource.ContextCreating> event to supply your own <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> instead of having a new <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> created.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a13db-190">Si el <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource.ContextCreating> no se controla el evento o el controlador no proporciona un <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext>, el <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource> crea uno según su configuración.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a13db-190">If the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource.ContextCreating> event is not handled or the handler does not provide an <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext>, the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource> creates one according to its configuration.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a13db-191">Cuando un <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> se proporciona para el <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource.ContextCreating> la misma instancia de evento, se asigna a la `Context` propiedad del objeto de evento de eventos posteriores.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a13db-191">When an <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> is provided to the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource.ContextCreating> event, the same instance is assigned to the `Context` property of the event object of successive events.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a13db-192">Para obtener más información, consulte [administración de ciclo de vida del contexto de objetos (EntityDataSource)](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/67bc2486-112c-47c3-b23f-0297f7ac2160).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a13db-192">For more information, see [Object Context Life-Cycle Management (EntityDataSource)](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/67bc2486-112c-47c3-b23f-0297f7ac2160).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a13db-193">Para obtener más información sobre el contexto del objeto, vea [resolución de identidades, administración de Estados y seguimiento de cambios](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/3bd49311-0e72-4ea4-8355-38fe57036ba0).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a13db-193">For more information about the object context, see [Identity Resolution, State Management, and Change Tracking](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/3bd49311-0e72-4ea4-8355-38fe57036ba0).</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="a13db-194">El ejemplo siguiente muestra cómo crear un <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> variable de la <xref:System.Web.UI.Page> objeto y asígnelo a la <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSourceContextCreatingEventArgs.Context%2A> propiedad de la <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSourceContextCreatingEventArgs> objeto.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a13db-194">The following example shows how to create an <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> variable of the <xref:System.Web.UI.Page> object and assign it to the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSourceContextCreatingEventArgs.Context%2A> property of the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSourceContextCreatingEventArgs> object.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
public partial class _Default : System.Web.UI.Page  
    {  
        AdventureWorksModel.AdventureWorksEntities objCtx =  
            new AdventureWorksModel.AdventureWorksEntities();  
  
        protected void EntityDataSource2_ContextCreating(object sender,   
            EntityDataSourceContextCreatingEventArgs e)  
        {  
            e.Context = objCtx;  
        }  
    }  
```
